Cozy restaurant nestled in Hyde Park with a gastro pub model. Menu items include quick eats like soup, salads, chips and dip and also chicken tenders. Hearty meals include Rotisserie Chicken and Cheeseburgers served on Italian bread instead of a traditional sesame bun. The staff are friendly and attentive but can easily misunderstand what you may ask for. I asked for the waitress what beers do they have she looked perplexed at 1st but then when I repeated my question, she muttered if two different beers. I was later joined by a friend on my visit and she asked the same question. She was given a drink list with all options of what they carried. This confused me. When seated while waiting on my lunch date, the staff was overly zealous approaching the table asking was I ready to order. Like 4+ times in a 15 minutes span. I understand being attentive but GEEZ. It made me feel the "if you won't buy anything then we may ask you to leave." kinda vibe. The food is ok. Just tad pricey to be just ok. I haven't had anything here that's made me rant and rave but it's fine for a quick chew and chat with a buddy. My friend ordered the hot wings and said they were tasty. The guacamole needs some love. Flavorless. Just creamy green mush. They are often out of other menu entrees as well at times. Popular items are Rotisserie Chicken and the chili. Which during one visit, me and my fiance order and they had neither. I do like the chicken tenders here tho.

I’ve been going to Mellow Yellow since they opened in 1976. However, I do not plan to return after my experience today. My husband and I waited patiently for the restaurant to open at 8 am for breakfast. At 8:03 am, the doors were not opened although staff was inside and should have been able to see us standing in front of the window. Finally, a young man came to the door and unlocked it. I reached for the second of the two entry door anticipating that he would say good morning and hold it so that I could follow him in. Instead, he allowed the door to just close in my face without any attempt to hold it. I was stunned that someone in the restaurant industry especially would lack general courtesy.  This has really left a strong impression for me of how Mellow Yellow has changed. Needless to say, after waiting in the area for 30 minutes to eat there we left immediately and went to the restaurant just down the street. Very disappointed with our old favorite, Mellow Yellow. Truly hope they will read this and teach their staff the basics of courtesy and kindness.

Been to Mellow Yellow back in the day... It's NOT the same place.  I ordered eggs and sausage.  Sausage was decent, but something was off with the eggs! I ordered veggie omelette... The Veggies were undercooked and I sensed the omelette had a "microwave" texture to it.  I studied under a chef and learned how to make omelettes,  you can tell the difference between one that is truly cooked in a skillet vs one that's been nuked in the microwave.  Anyway...  like an hour later, I got sick on my stomach!!!!  Something is definitely OFF about the place now.  I feel like either it's the COOKS or the MANAGEMENT, but the food has lost that personalized touch,  lacks seasoning and feels "thrown together."  The only reason I am giving TWO STARS is because the WAITSTAFF was cordial, kind and accommodating.  But, I am afraid, sadly... I won't be back. And, that's unfortunate, because Mellow Yellow was a Hyde Park staple and a place you could count on for excellent, high-quality food.

I've been to Mellow Yellow before and since my wife and I were in the neighborhood this afternoon, I suggested going there. She had never been but I assured her she would not be disappointed and the cold two block walk in the snow would be worth it.... HOWEVER it was not! We were the ONLY two people there and sat for TEN minutes or more and didn't even get water. One lady was cleaning and two others seemed to be having a meeting with their manager. We also saw a guy in a lavender shirt on an an apron that looked like the guy in the photos on the wall. He didn't acknowledge us either. Just came in a few times to watch CNN. My wife got up at one point to remind them we were waiting but it didn't matter. I was so upset I decided to leave. As we were leaving I thought that the three ladies would acknowledge us, apologize, convince us to stay.... HOWEVER, they didn't even look at us. This had to be the worst customer service I've gotten in my life. Not to mention this is my BIRTHDAY weekend and I choose to go there and my wife and I were treated like we were invisible to everyone and we were the only customers there. Not happy! If it were possible to give no stars, I would have.
